Articles.Content:
Admittedly I am using dev versions of MechJeb. On Sunday everything was fine. Today I get to "Loading part upgrades" and the game crashes. I deleted the folder for the MechJeb2-2.6.0.0-698. The game booted. I put back the folder for MechJeb2-2.5.9.0-660 and the game still  crashed. I had been using that build for months without any problem.

I have an elaborate saved game, but I can't stop but wonder if it has something to do with the language update.

I don't want to delete my current game just to find I still have the game error. Lord knows I have made enough ship design errors in it, and I will delete it. But every thing was working on Sunday.

What happened?
KSP was updated to 1.3 (if you have it on Steam, it may have updated without you knowing). It's crashing on modded installs, it may be that Mechjeb is one/the curprit.
MechJeb is not updated to 1.3 yet. Stay on 1.2.2 or play without MJ until Sarbian updates

I was interrupted in the middle of an epic mission because of this.... no way to tell Steam not to update :-( .  While Sarbian releases something official and more polished, here is a patched version of MechJeb2 that runs on KSP 1.3: 

https://github.com/alcidesv/MechJeb2/releases/download/2.6.1/MechJeb-2.6.1-6-gdcb9f2c.zip

I also opened a pull request to the official repo.
MJ is crashing everyone's game. So is KER. It seems that part mods (KWR, SpaceY, etc) work fine.

12 minutes ago, icantmakemodels said:

MJ is crashing everyone's game. So is KER. It seems that part mods (KWR, SpaceY, etc) work fine.

This is standard behavior after a version update with KSP.  (Or really, a lot of things in the computer world...)

The game boots all the way for me but I cant find any of the parts that are supposed to come with the mod. I just got ksp for my computer today specifically for mechjeb. Any way anyone can help? I had the same problem but the link provided above definitely helped. Now I just don't know how to get it to work.
Yes I did copy and paste the file into the gamedata folder. Incase anyone asks.

Hi.

Along with many other mods, Mechjeb is probably broken with KSP v1.3. If you bought via Steam, you can download a previous version such as 1.2.2 by going to the game properties, selecting the "betas" tab and opting into one of the available previous versions. The KSP store should have 1.2.2 as one of the available links. I'm actually not sure what previous versions GOG has available. As for when it'll be updated to version 1.3, I'll quote the maintainer:

(I think he's a bit busy)

@therealkylexy

Just to cover the absolute basics, MechJeb is a part that you add to your ship. It is found in the Command section.

 

It has close to zero mass and can be put anywhere, but it does have the light, so you can use it as a sort of free indicator for docking ports. :-)

I hope that helps a bit. Ask more specific questions if you are still having problems.
FYI....I ran in to this issue also and that is because CKAN is showing Mechjeb compatible with 1.3.9 KSP so a bunch of people are probably going to get caught by this if using CKAN.
